You want to know how we can work with a variable x to work out the factorial value. We will write a while loop to work through the numbers. The while loop will work until we reach one. We will multiply the result with each number we see. This way we will know the answer. We will now show how it works with x equal to seven. The while loop will work well for this task. We will now write the code to work as we want.

```javascript
let x = 7;
let result = 1;
while (x > 1) {
  result = result * x;
  x = x - 1;
}
console.log(result);
```
